    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-07-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-07-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="220" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Baker</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-07-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 25,
                                1893</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Adee instructs Mr. Baker to present, either jointly with the other
                            diplomatic representatives or in a separate note to the titular
                            Government a protest against the waging of hostilities without warning,
                            whereby foreigners are endangered.</p>
            </div>
